{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":509200,"name":"wakasugi hakata","username":"WakasugiHa47584","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/w/edb3f5/{size}.png","created_at":"2026-04-14T05:45:36.594Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ca class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/taycaldwell\"\u003e@taycaldwell\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nCould you offer any help regarding this please?\u003cbr\u003e\nWhat’s your App ID?\u003cbr\u003e\n32636743\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat endpoint are you using?\u003cbr\u003e\nPOST /2/tweets\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat API version are you on?\u003cbr\u003e\nv2\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAre you using a library or SDK? Which one?\u003cbr\u003e\ntwitter-api-v2 (Node.js)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat is the issue?\u003cbr\u003e\nMy app is on the Pay-Per-Use plan with $9.96 credits available. OAuth 2.0 PKCE token exchange succeeds and the token is recognized as a User Context token (response header `x-access-level: read-write`), but POST /2/tweets consistently returns 403 Forbidden with `“You are not permitted to perform this action.”`\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe new Developer Console shows the app only under **“Pay Per Use”** as a **Standalone App** — there is **no “Projects \u0026amp; Apps” section** available. I suspect this is the root cause, since v2 write endpoints require the app to be attached to a Project (client-not-enrolled).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSteps to reproduce the issue\u003cbr\u003e\nStep 1: Authenticate via OAuth 2.0 PKCE with scopes \u003ccode\u003etweet.write media.write users.read tweet.read offline.access\u003c/code\u003e — succeeds, user access token is returned.\u003cbr\u003e\nStep 2: Call `POST /2/tweets` with the user access token — returns 403 Forbidden.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat is the error message?\u003cbr\u003e\nFrom the library (twitter-api-v2):\u003cbr\u003e\n```json\u003cbr\u003e\n{\u003cbr\u003e\n“detail”: “You are not permitted to perform this action.”,\u003cbr\u003e\n“type”: “about:blank”,\u003cbr\u003e\n“title”: “Forbidden”,\u003cbr\u003e\n“status”: 403\u003cbr\u003e\n}\u003cbr\u003e\n```\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eResponse headers include `x-access-level: read-write`, `x-rate-limit-remaining: 99`, `api-version: 2.161`.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDirect curl test with the same token returns:\u003cbr\u003e\n```json\u003cbr\u003e\n{\u003cbr\u003e\n“title”: “Unsupported Authentication”,\u003cbr\u003e\n“detail”: “Authenticating with OAuth 2.0 Application-Only is forbidden for this endpoint. Supported authentication types are [OAuth 1.0a User Context, OAuth 2.0 User Context].”,\u003cbr\u003e\n“status”: 403\u003cbr\u003e\n}\u003cbr\u003e\n```\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis strongly suggests the app is not properly enrolled as a Project-attached app, so X’s API rejects the write.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhen did it start?\u003cbr\u003e\nThe app has never successfully posted. It was created on the Pay-Per-Use plan from the start, and POST /2/tweets has returned 403 from the first attempt.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat have you tried to troubleshoot?\u003cbr\u003e\nVerified \u003cstrong\u003eApp permissions\u003c/strong\u003e = “Read and write” in User authentication settings\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eVerified \u003cstrong\u003eType of App\u003c/strong\u003e = “Web App, Automated App or Bot”\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eVerified OAuth 2.0 scopes: \u003ccode\u003etweet.read\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003etweet.write\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003emedia.write\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eusers.read\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eoffline.access\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eRe-authenticated\u003c/strong\u003e (disconnected and ran a fresh OAuth 2.0 PKCE flow) — new token issued, same 403\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eConfirmed \u003cstrong\u003ecredits available\u003c/strong\u003e: $9.96\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eConfirmed \u003cstrong\u003enot rate-limited\u003c/strong\u003e: \u003ccode\u003ex-rate-limit-remaining: 99\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eConfirmed \u003cstrong\u003eaccount is healthy\u003c/strong\u003e: email and phone verified, manual tweeting from the same account (@-redacted) works fine\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2026-04-14T05:45:36.594Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":76,"reads":15,"readers_count":14,"score":378.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":262696,"topic_slug":"post-2-tweets-return-403-you-are-not-permitted-to-perform-this-action-on-pay-per-use-plan-with-oauth-2-0","display_username":"wakasugi hakata","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":199805,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":false,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/post-2-tweets-return-403-you-are-not-permitted-to-perform-this-action-on-pay-per-use-plan-with-oauth-2-0/262696/1","can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true,"can_vote":false},{"id":509366,"name":"Taylor","username":"taycaldwell","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/devcommunity.x.com/taycaldwell/{size}/120545_2.png","created_at":"2026-04-15T02:48:46.230Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThe root cause for the error is outlined in it’s description:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003eAuthenticating with OAuth 2.0 Application-Only is forbidden for this endpoint.\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou are currently using your Bearer Token (App-only authentication) to authenticate the API request. You will need to use user context authentication instead.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou can either do so by configuring OAuth1.0a with your Consumer Key, Consumer Secret, Access Token, and Access Token secret if you wish to post on behalf of your own account, or implement either the 3-legged OAuth1.0 or PKCE OAuth2.0 flow to post on behalf of another user.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePlease refer to our authentication documentation for more details.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2026-04-15T02:48:46.230Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":9,"readers_count":8,"score":6.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":262696,"topic_slug":"post-2-tweets-return-403-you-are-not-permitted-to-perform-this-action-on-pay-per-use-plan-with-oauth-2-0","display_username":"Taylor","primary_group_name":"x-staff","flair_name":"x-staff","flair_url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/original/3X/e/a/ea97b7b22cd08a7e2774a9f697a928260efff823.jpeg","flair_bg_color":"000000","flair_color":"","flair_group_id":42,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"X Staff","title_is_group":true,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":174688,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":false,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/post-2-tweets-return-403-you-are-not-permitted-to-perform-this-action-on-pay-per-use-plan-with-oauth-2-0/262696/2","can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":509376,"name":"wakasugi hakata","username":"WakasugiHa47584","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/w/edb3f5/{size}.png","created_at":"2026-04-15T05:17:40.069Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThank you for the quick response.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHowever, I want to clarify that I am already implementing OAuth 2.0 PKCE, not App-only authentication. Let me provide more detail so we can narrow down the root cause:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMy current setup (OAuth 2.0 PKCE — confirmed)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAuthorization URL generation (twitter-api-v2 library):\u003cbr\u003e\nconst { url, codeVerifier, state } = client.generateOAuth2AuthLink(\u003cbr\u003e\nredirectUri,\u003cbr\u003e\n{ scope: [‘tweet.read’, ‘tweet.write’, ‘media.write’, ‘users.read’, ‘offline.access’] }\u003cbr\u003e\n)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eToken exchange with PKCE code_verifier (not client_credentials grant):\u003cbr\u003e\nconst result = await client.loginWithOAuth2({\u003cbr\u003e\ncode,                // received from callback\u003cbr\u003e\ncodeVerifier,        // PKCE verifier (proves this is user-context, not app-only)\u003cbr\u003e\nredirectUri,\u003cbr\u003e\n})\u003cbr\u003e\nconst { accessToken, refreshToken, expiresIn } = result\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTweet posting with the user access token from step 2:\u003cbr\u003e\nconst userClient = new TwitterApi(accessToken)\u003cbr\u003e\nawait userClient.v2.tweet({ text: ‘…’ })\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEvidence this is a user token (not App-only)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe token was obtained through /2/oauth2/token with grant_type=authorization_code, code, and code_verifier — not grant_type=client_credentials.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe response header on the 403 includes x-access-level: read-write — which is only returned when X recognizes the token as user-context.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUser is successfully authorized: \u003ca class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/demoai59382\"\u003e@DemoAi59382\u003c/a\u003e is attached to the token (confirmed via the Developer Console showing the issued token with scopes tweet.write, media.write,\u003cbr\u003e\nusers.read, tweet.read for this account).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYet X API still responds as if it is App-only\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eVia twitter-api-v2: 403 “You are not permitted to perform this action.” with x-access-level: read-write\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eVia direct curl with the same token: 403 “Authenticating with OAuth 2.0 Application-Only is forbidden for this endpoint.”\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMy hypothesis\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBecause my app on the Pay-Per-Use plan only appears under “Apps → Pay Per Use” as a Standalone App (the new Developer Console has no “Projects \u0026amp; Apps” section), the app is\u003cbr\u003e\nnot enrolled in a Project. Since v2 write endpoints require an app to be attached to a Project, X’s API rejects the user token as “not permitted” — even though the token\u003cbr\u003e\nitself is a valid user-context token from the PKCE flow.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMy questions\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCan you confirm whether Pay-Per-Use Standalone Apps are capable of posting via POST /2/tweets at all?\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIf yes, what additional configuration is needed on the app side?\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2026-04-15T05:17:40.069Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":9,"readers_count":8,"score":1.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":262696,"topic_slug":"post-2-tweets-return-403-you-are-not-permitted-to-perform-this-action-on-pay-per-use-plan-with-oauth-2-0","display_username":"wakasugi hakata","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":174688,"username":"taycaldwell","name":"Taylor","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/devcommunity.x.com/taycaldwell/{size}/120545_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":199805,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":false,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/post-2-tweets-return-403-you-are-not-permitted-to-perform-this-action-on-pay-per-use-plan-with-oauth-2-0/262696/3","can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":509512,"name":"Taylor","username":"taycaldwell","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/devcommunity.x.com/taycaldwell/{size}/120545_2.png","created_at":"2026-04-16T02:40:36.136Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eYour app (ID 32636743) is correctly enrolled in Pay Per Use and supports \u003ccode\u003ePOST /2/tweets\u003c/code\u003e up to 2M posts/month.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe 403 stems from two app restrictions visible in your console/plan:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eReplies only when mentioned\u003c/strong\u003e: Your app can only post replies to @-mentions, not original content.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCashtag limit\u003c/strong\u003e: One cashtag per post max.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor full posting, upgrade your Pay Per Use tier (spend more credits) or apply for Enterprise. Also, your curl uses an app-only Bearer token—switch to \u003ccode\u003eAuthorization: Bearer \u0026lt;user_access_token\u0026gt;\u003c/code\u003e from PKCE.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://docs.x.com/x-api/posts/create-post.md\"\u003eCreate Post docs\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://docs.x.com/x-api/getting-started/pricing.md\"\u003ePricing\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2026-04-16T02:40:36.136Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":8,"readers_count":7,"score":26.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":262696,"topic_slug":"post-2-tweets-return-403-you-are-not-permitted-to-perform-this-action-on-pay-per-use-plan-with-oauth-2-0","display_username":"Taylor","primary_group_name":"x-staff","flair_name":"x-staff","flair_url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/original/3X/e/a/ea97b7b22cd08a7e2774a9f697a928260efff823.jpeg","flair_bg_color":"000000","flair_color":"","flair_group_id":42,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.x.com/x-api/getting-started/pricing.md","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":2},{"url":"https://docs.x.com/x-api/posts/create-post.md","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":"X Staff","title_is_group":true,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":174688,"hidden":false,"trust_level":4,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":false,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/post-2-tweets-return-403-you-are-not-permitted-to-perform-this-action-on-pay-per-use-plan-with-oauth-2-0/262696/4","can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":true,"topic_accepted_answer":true},{"id":509651,"name":"wakasugi hakata","username":"WakasugiHa47584","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/w/edb3f5/{size}.png","created_at":"2026-04-17T01:09:09.869Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi, I understand the issue now. I fixed the hashtag by using only one cashtag, and the post went through successfully.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThank you very much!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":7,"updated_at":"2026-0